    "raw": "Build an unsupervised pipeline (not IDF/BM25, not supervised ST fine-tuning) that reads our documents and todo text, embeds chunks with sentence-transformers (or compatible dense embedder), and derives terms/phrases that are semantically important in vector space for our domain.\n\nContext from design discussion:\n- Hash embedder and lexical boosts are insufficient for semantic vocabulary discovery.\n- sentence-transformers encode() is the engine only; importance scoring is our pipeline.\n- NOT Apple Create ML / NLContextualEmbedding.\n- NOT document-frequency IDF scores; importance means discriminative/salient in embedding geometry (e.g. term vectors aligned with doc/cluster centroids and far from global corpus centroid; KeyBERT-style doc-term cosine; cluster representatives after UMAP/HDBSCAN).\n\nRelates to todo-embedding branch (sqlite + search) but this ticket is the separate semantic vocabulary layer: corpus ingest, candidate phrase mining, embed, score, persist term table, expose via todo.py (e.g. terms list / terms for doc / search boost hook).\n\nStart after or alongside merging todo-embedding sqlite storage."
  },
